Project: Customer Segmentation¶

Goal: Segment customers into 3–4 meaningful clusters each year—based on standardized revenue growth, purchase frequency, and average spend, to analyze their migration across 2021, 2022, and 2023.¶

Build Segmentation Model¶

In [98]:
# Pivot: total revenue by Customer Id and Year
pivot1 = data.pivot_table(index='ID', columns='Year', values='Revenue')

# pivot: total purchases and spend by Customer Id and Year 
pivot_purchases = data.pivot_table(index='ID', columns='Year', values='Number of Purchases')
pivot_spend     = data.pivot_table(index='ID', columns='Year', values='Average Spend')

# growth rates and append end-year Purchases & Spend
# Revenue Growth Rate = (Revenue EndYear  Revenue StartYear)  Revenue StartYear  100

# 20202021
table_2020_2021 = (
    ((pivot1[2021] - pivot1[2020]) / pivot1[2020])
    .reset_index(name='growth rate 2020-2021')
)
table_2020_2021['Number of Purchases'] = table_2020_2021['ID'].map(pivot_purchases[2021])
table_2020_2021['Average Spend']        = table_2020_2021['ID'].map(pivot_spend[2021])


# 20212022
table_2021_2022 = (
    ((pivot1[2022] - pivot1[2021]) / pivot1[2021])
    .reset_index(name='growth rate 2021-2022')
)
table_2021_2022['Number of Purchases'] = table_2021_2022['ID'].map(pivot_purchases[2022])
table_2021_2022['Average Spend']        = table_2021_2022['ID'].map(pivot_spend[2022])


# 20222023
table_2022_2023 = (
    ((pivot1[2023] - pivot1[2022]) / pivot1[2022])
    .reset_index(name='growth rate 2022-2023')
)
table_2022_2023['Number of Purchases'] = table_2022_2023['ID'].map(pivot_purchases[2023])
table_2022_2023['Average Spend']        = table_2022_2023['ID'].map(pivot_spend[2023])

#Output tables

print(table_2020_2021, end="\n\n")

print("2022")
print(table_2021_2022, end="\n\n")

print("2023")
print(table_2022_2023)

# Univariate Distributions & Outlier
def plot_univariate(table, growth_col, year):
    feats = ['Number of Purchases', 'Average Spend', growth_col]
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(feats), 2, figsize=(12, 4*len(feats)))
    
    for i, col in enumerate(feats):
        sns.histplot(table[col].dropna(), kde=True, ax=axes[i,0])
        axes[i,0].set_title(f"{col} distribution ({year})")
        sns.boxplot(x=table[col].dropna(), ax=axes[i,1])
        axes[i,1].set_title(f"{col} boxplot ({year})")
    
    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In [105]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering


# Use only normalized data for clustering and output
X = table_2020_2021_normalized[features2021].values

wcss = [] # wcss: Within-cluster sum of squares
silhouette_scores = []
hier_silhouette    = []                              
K_range = range(2, 7)
for k in K_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=1234, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(X)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    sil_score = silhouette_score(X, kmeans.labels_)
    silhouette_scores.append(sil_score)

# Hierarchical (Ward linkage) for the same K
    hc = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=k, linkage='ward')     
    labels_h = hc.fit_predict(X)
    hier_silhouette.append(silhouette_score(X, labels_h))  



fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))

#  Elbow plot
axes[0].plot(list(K_range), wcss, marker='o')
axes[0].set_title('WCSS vs. Number of Clusters')
axes[0].set_xlabel('K')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Within-Cluster Sum of Squares')

#  Silhouette comparison
axes[1].plot(list(K_range), silhouette_scores, marker='o', label='K-means')
axes[1].plot(list(K_range), hier_silhouette,    marker='^', label='Hierarchical')  
axes[1].set_title('Silhouette Score vs. Number of Clusters')
axes[1].set_xlabel('K')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Silhouette Score') 
axes[1].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Use only normalized data for clustering and output
X = table_2021_2022_normalized[features2022].values

wcss = [] # wcss: Within-cluster sum of squares
silhouette_scores = []
hier_silhouette = [] 

K_range = range(2, 7)
for k in K_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=1234, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(X)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    sil_score = silhouette_score(X, kmeans.labels_)
    silhouette_scores.append(sil_score)


# Hierarchical (Ward linkage) for the same K
    hc = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=k, linkage='ward')     
    labels_h = hc.fit_predict(X)
    hier_silhouette.append(silhouette_score(X, labels_h))  



fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))

#  Elbow plot
axes[0].plot(list(K_range), wcss, marker='o')
axes[0].set_title('WCSS vs. Number of Clusters')
axes[0].set_xlabel('K')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Within-Cluster Sum of Squares')

#  Silhouette comparison
axes[1].plot(list(K_range), silhouette_scores, marker='o', label='K-means')
axes[1].plot(list(K_range), hier_silhouette,    marker='^', label='Hierarchical')  
axes[1].set_title('Silhouette Score vs. Number of Clusters')
axes[1].set_xlabel('K')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Silhouette Score') 
axes[1].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Calculate year-to-year movement (migration)
merged['move_21_22'] = merged['Cluster2022'] - merged['Cluster2021']
merged['move_22_23'] = merged['Cluster2023'] - merged['Cluster2022']

# Improvement index for each step
merged['improve_21_22'] = merged['move_21_22'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x > 0 else (-1 if x < 0 else 0))
merged['improve_22_23'] = merged['move_22_23'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x > 0 else (-1 if x < 0 else 0))

# Migration index (sum of improvements)
merged['migration_index_21_23'] = merged['improve_21_22'] + merged['improve_22_23']

# Overall movement (from start to end year) 
merged['move_21_23'] = merged['Cluster2023'] - merged['Cluster2021']

# Frequency of cluster migration
merged['change_21_22'] = (merged['Cluster2021'] != merged['Cluster2022']).astype(int)
merged['change_22_23'] = (merged['Cluster2022'] != merged['Cluster2023']).astype(int)
merged['migration_frequency_index'] = merged['change_21_22'] + merged['change_22_23']

# Select and display combined summary table
summary_table = merged[['ID', 
                        'Cluster2021', 
                        'Cluster2022', 
                        'Cluster2023', 
                        'move_21_22', 
                        'move_22_23', 
                        'move_21_23', 
                        'migration_index_21_23',
                        'change_21_22',
                        'change_22_23',
                        'migration_frequency_index']]
